      "content": "The Civil Rights Movement achieved significant milestones, such as the passage of the Civil Rights Act of 1964 and the Voting Rights Act of 1965, which dismantled some of the most egregious forms of institutionalized racism. However, despite these gains, the movement ultimately fell short of achieving true systemic change, as many of the underlying power structures and inequalities persisted. The legacy of segregation and racism continues to affect communities of color today, and the movement's focus on incremental reform rather than radical transformation has been widely criticized.",
